House 21 in Vienna
The pavilion moved
By Ingeborg Wiensowski
An architectural history with ups and downs and a happy ending, the 1958 Brussels Austrian World Exhibition Pavilion won awards, was in Vienna for a museum, was left empty and fell apart.
Now it reopens as an exhibition house.
The modern postgerra architecture is passionate, the clear forms, the glass halls, the bold curves and the new construction materials, typical of the thinking about technical progress, for which, the Austrian pavilion of the architect Karl Schwanzer for the universal exhibition of Brussels of 1958 is a suitable and well-known example.
