In many places, rooks are considered &quot;problem birds&quot; - these highly intelligent animals are not driven out of cities for long, experts say.
Some like them, others want to get rid of them very quickly, the rooks have been in the image of the city for years, but in many municipalities the complaints of the neighbors accumulate about the filth and the noise of the animals.
